'''

Screen switching function

We need a function that picks which frame we need to show. Originally
I had the idea to build this into other functions, but I had many 
issues. After calling upon AI, I settled upon building a helper 
function whos entire purpose is to take an input 'frame_to_show'
which is the exact frame that we want to display at the moment and
do the following:

1) turn off all other frames

2) display 'frame_to_show'

The input should always be one of start_menu_frame, main_frame, 
or end_screen_frame.

This function is super useful and will end up being called in 
several other functions. 

'''
def show_frame(frame_to_show):
    # stop displaying all frames
    start_menu_frame.pack_forget()
    main_frame.pack_forget()
    end_screen_frame.pack_forget()
    #display the one frame we tell it to
    frame_to_show.pack()

'''

I needed a new tkinter compatible choos_difficulty fucntion. This is because of the 
way that tkinter loops work. My jupyter notebooks code worked via a loop that was
waiting for user input, but tkinter works with a main loop, which runs a function
when the user presses a button. So I need to make a new function which gets called
instantaeously rather than waiting for user input.

This function also updates current_state and lives in the main_frame,
then displays the main frame once the user has selected difficulty

'''

def choose_difficulty(difficulty):
   
   # establishing global variables so that we can change them in this function
   global secret_word, current_state, lives_used, letters_guessed

   # choosing the secret word using the previous function we made
   secret_word = word_picking_func(difficulty)

   # setting the current state to a string of underscores with the same length as 
   # the secret word
   current_state = ' '.join('_' * len(secret_word))

   # resetting lives used, letters guessed for the new round
   lives_used = 0
   letters_guessed = []


   # resetting the current_state being displayed in the main game 
   current_state_display_label.config(text = current_state)
   lives_label.config(text = f'You have used {lives_used} / 6 lives')

   letters_guessed_label.config(text = 'Guessed letters: ')

   # clearing hangman
   hangman_canvas.delete('all')

   # redrawing canvas
   hangman_canvas.create_line(20, 230, 120, 230)   
   hangman_canvas.create_line(50, 230, 50, 20)     
   hangman_canvas.create_line(50, 20, 130, 20)  
   hangman_canvas.create_line(130, 20, 130, 50)

   # using helper function to display the main game frame
   show_frame(main_frame)

'''

HANGMAN DRAWING FUNCTION

This function takes as input the number of lives, and draws on 
a different body part based on how many lives. We start with the 
head, then torso, then arms and finally legs. Crucially, a 
body part thats been drawn on does not dissapear until we clear
the screen, so calling the function seevral times will draw 
multiple limbs and not replace them. 

### AI USED TO GENERATE LOCATION OF LIMBS ###

'''

def draw_body_part(lives_used):
   if lives_used == 1:
      hangman_canvas.create_oval(110,50,150,90)
   elif lives_used == 2:
      hangman_canvas.create_line(130, 90, 130, 150)         
   elif lives_used == 3:
      hangman_canvas.create_line(130, 100, 100, 130)         
   elif lives_used == 4:
      hangman_canvas.create_line(130, 100, 160, 130)       
   elif lives_used == 5:
      hangman_canvas.create_line(130, 150, 100, 190)        
   elif lives_used == 6:
      hangman_canvas.create_line(130, 150, 160, 190) 


'''

We now need to create a new function that deals with the user's guess.
In my original notebook implementation (v1.1.0) this function was the
main loop, but in this new tkinter implementation we're not waiting
for input, the function must trigger when the player presses the 
'submit' button. 

The function wille essentially do the same thing otherwise though,
in particular it must:

1) read player's input

2) pass input through letter_validation_function

3) if letter_validation_function returns invalid input, display an 
error message.

4) If the letter has already been guessed, we must flag it

5) For a valid guess we must
 - add letter to letters_guessed
 - call letter_checking function 
 - update current_state and lives_used
 - clear old error messages
 - clear entry box

6) update current_state and lives_label on the gui.

7) Check whether the game has ended

8) if game hasnt ended, do nothing

9) if game has ended

 - update all of the labels on the end screen
 - update global statistics
 - call show_frame(end_screen_frame) to display the ending screen

'''


def guess_letter():
   
   # the function does not need inputs, everything it needs is a 
   # global paramater
   global current_state, lives_used, letters_guessed
   global games_played, games_won, games_lost

   # step 1 reading input

   # getting a guess from the letter input box
   input = guess_entry.get()

   # step 2 passing input through letter validation

   letter, is_valid = letter_validation_function(input)

   # step 3 if letter_validation_function reads invalid,
   # we reprompt

   if not is_valid:
      #displaying error message
      message_label.config(text = 'Please enter a single letter')
      #clearing everything in user_guessed box
      guess_entry.delete(0, tk.END)
      return # end the function early so we dont run future code
   
   # step 4 if the letter has already been guessed, we inform 
   # the user and reprompt 
 
   if letter in letters_guessed:
      message_label.config(text = 'You have already guessed that letter, please guess again')
      guess_entry.delete(0, tk.END)
      return
   
   # step 5 now the letter is valid so we can proceed with the game
   
   # adding letter to list of guessed letters

   letters_guessed.append(letter)

   #updating current_state and lives_used
   current_state, lives_used = letter_checking_function(secret_word,
                                letter, current_state, lives_used)
   
   # draw appropriate hangman body part
   draw_body_part(lives_used)

   # removing any left over message text and clearing guess box
   message_label.config(text = '')
   guess_entry.delete(0, tk.END)

   # step 6 update screen display

   current_state_display_label.config(text = current_state)
   lives_label.config(text = f'You have usd {lives_used} / 6 lives')
   letters_guessed_label.config(text = f"Guessed letters: {', '.join(letters_guessed)}")

   # step 7 check if the game has ended
   
   # first condition of game ending is player running out of lives
   if lives_used >= 6:
      # updating label to display loss
      win_or_loss_label.config(text="You lost :(")
      #revealing secret word
      reveal_label.config(text=f"The word was: {secret_word}")
      #updating global stats
      games_played += 1
      games_lost += 1
      stats_label.config(text=f"Games played: {games_played} | Won: {games_won} | Lost: {games_lost}")
      # using helper function to move onto end game screen after
      # waiting a bit of time to let the drawn hangman settle
      root.after(2000,lambda: show_frame(end_screen_frame))

   # second game end condition is '_' not appearing in current state anymore
   # overall same logic as the notebook version
   elif '_' not in current_state:
      #updating label to display win message
      win_or_loss_label.config(text = 'You Won!')
      reveal_label.config(text = f'The word was: {secret_word}')
      #updating global statistics
      games_played += 1
      games_won += 1
      stats_label.config(text=f"Games played: {games_played} | Won: {games_won} | Lost: {games_lost}")
      # using helper function to move to end screen
      show_frame(end_screen_frame)
    
   # If the game has not ended, nothing else happens. We dont 
   # need to wrap it in a loop anymore, ebcause this function
   # is triggered by th press of a button

#initialising the start menu as the first frame
show_frame(start_menu_frame)

#launching tkinter loop
root.mainloop()